.TH "sys_sched_setaffinity" 9 "sys_sched_setaffinity" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
sys_sched_setaffinity \- set the CPU affinity of a process
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "long" sys_sched_setaffinity
.BI "(pid_t pid "  ","
.BI "unsigned int len "  ","
.BI "unsigned long __user * user_mask_ptr "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pid" 12
pid of the process
.IP "len" 12
length in bytes of the bitmask pointed to by user_mask_ptr
.IP "user_mask_ptr" 12
user-space pointer to the new CPU mask
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success. An error code otherwise.
